        <defect>
            <para>This Recall applies to 2500, 2600, 8100, 8200, 9600, and 9700 models built from 04/21/1995 through
                05/03/1995 with tractor brake code 04092, without code 04WBN. If the vehicle has code 04WBN, Omit
                Bobtail Proportioning, no repair is necessary.
            </para>
            <para>Bobtail proportioning brake systems were made standard on heavy duty tractor models to provide
                improved brake balance when running in the bobtail mode. Because of a coding error, some 2000, 8000, and
                9000 cabover vehicles may have had a portion of the brake system improperly plumbed, which would affect
                the brakes on the rear axle.
            </para>
            <para>Should the brake system not be properly plumbed, it would be detrimental to the stopping ability, and
                in some cases, controllability of the vehicle because the rear axle brakes of the tractor would not be
                doing their share of the braking. This could result in an accident, causing personal injury or property
                damage.
            </para>
            <para>Additionally, accelerated brake lining and drum wear could result on the tractor front axle and
                trailer wheels.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Owner Notification</title>
            </para>
            <para>Owners will be notified of this campaign on their vehicles by Navistar. A listing of owner names and
                addresses has been furnished to the involved dealers to enable dealers to follow up with owners to have
                the vehicles corrected. You must limit the use of this listing to this campaign since the list may
                contain information obtained from state motor vehicle registration records and the use of such motor
                vehicle registration data for purposes other than this campaign is a violation of law in several states.
            </para>
        </defect>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE - 2500, 2600, 8100, and 8200 Models with BP-R1 (Brake Proportioning Relay Valve),
                CR-18 (ABS Controller with BTP), or AT-2 (ABS Controller with BTP and Automatic Traction Control)
            </title>
            <para>Reference
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9550801">Figure 1</hotlnk>. For vehicles
                <emph type="bold">without ABS,</emph>
                check rear crossmember to determine whether the vehicle was built with an R-12 Relay Valve or a BP-R1
                Brake Proportioning Relay Valve. If vehicle has an R-12 Relay Valve, brake system is okay and no further
                action is required.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9550801" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9550801" filename="../recallfigures/g9550801.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>For vehicles
                <emph type="bold">with ABS,</emph>
                check left rear sidemember to determine if the vehicle was built with a CR-17, CR-18 or AT-2 Controller.
                If vehicle has a CR-17 Controller, the brake system is okay and no further action is required.
            </para>
            <para>If vehicle has either a BP-R1 Valve or a CR-18 or AT-2 Controller, proceed with the following steps:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that 3/8 inch red tube is present and connected to the top port of the BP-R1
                    valve, the CR-18 or AT-2 Controller if vehicle has ABS, and to the air manifold on the cab firewall.
                    Reference Item 2 in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>. If the 3/8 inch red tube is missing, tubing must be
                    installed as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Use parts as listed in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9550802" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9550802" filename="../recallfigures/g9550802.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Only black bulk tubing is available in Service Parts.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that the 3/8 inch red tube (formed), Item 4 in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>, is present inside cab under dash from air manifold on
                    firewall to tee with 3/8 inch red tubes at other two ports. If 3/8 inch red tube (formed) is
                    missing, it must be installed as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Use parts as listed in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550802">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE - 9000 Cabover Models with BP-R1 (Brake Proportioning Relay Valve), CR-18 (ABS
                Controller with BTP), or AT-2 (ABS Controller with BTP and Automatic Traction Control)
            </title>
            <para>Reference
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9550801">Figure 1</hotlnk>. For vehicles
                <emph type="bold">without ABS,</emph>
                check rear crossmember to determine whether the vehicle was built with an R-12 Relay Valve or a BP-R1
                Brake Proportioning Relay Valve. If vehicle has an R-12 Relay Valve, brake system is okay and no further
                action is required.
            </para>
            <para>For vehicles
                <emph type="bold">with ABS,</emph>
                check left rear sidemember to determine if the vehicle was built with a CR-17, CR-18 or AT-2 Controller.
                If vehicle has a CR-17 Controller, the brake system is okay and no further action is required.
            </para>
            <para>If vehicle has either a BP-R1 Valve or a CR-18 or AT-2 Controller, proceed with the following steps:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that 3/8 inch red tube is present and connected to the top port of the BP-R1
                    valve, the CR-18 or AT-2 Controller if vehicle has ABS, and to the air manifold under the cab.
                    Reference Item 5 in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550803">Figure 3</hotlnk>. If the 3/8 inch red tube is missing, tubing must be
                    installed as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550803">Figure 3</hotlnk>. Use parts as listed in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550803">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9550803" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9550803" filename="../recallfigures/g9550803.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Only black bulk tubing is available in Service Parts.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the 3/8 inch red tube is installed from the BP-R1 Valve, CR-18 or AT-2 Controller to
                    the cab air manifold, an air check must be made to verify the installation of the 3/8 inch red tube
                    from the air manifold to the Tractor Protection Valve between the cab floors.
                </para>
                <para>AIR CHECK:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Temporarily plug emergency (red) trailer hose glad hand bracket with 1/4 inch bolt,
                        flat washer and nut as shown in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9550804">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9550804" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9550804" filename="../recallfigures/g9550804.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install emergency (red) trailer glad hand in glad hand holding bracket.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Build air pressure to governor cut out.
                        <emph type="bold">Leave engine running</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">PUSH IN</emph>
                        RED Trailer Air Supply knob on dash.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect 3/8 inch red tube at BP-R1 Valve, CR-18 or AT-2 Controller and determine
                        if air is exhausting.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If air exhausts, the tube is installed from the Tractor Protection Valve to the air
                        manifold between the cab floors and the system is okay.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>The 3/8 inch red tube at the BP-R1 Valve, CR-18 or AT-2 Controller must be reconnected
                                and the bolt in the glad hand bracket must be removed.
                                <emph type="bold">If air does not exhaust, do not reconnect red tube or remove bolt in
                                    glad hand bracket at this time.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If no air exhausts when Step 2.d. is performed, then the 3/8 inch red tube is
                        missing from the Tractor Protection Valve to the air manifold and Steps 3 through 13 must be
                        performed.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the 3/8 inch red tube between the cab floors, it will be necessary to remove
                    the driver's seat, roll back the floor mat, and remove the floor access panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the driver's seat, it will first be necessary to disconnect the air lines and
                    seat belts to the seat.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts holding the driver's seat to the floor and remove seat from vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove necessary hardware so floor mat can be rolled back out of the way.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove floor access panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 3/8 inch tubing from tractor protection tee to air manifold in the cab floor. Be
                    sure to connect to the opposite side of the port used for the 3/8 inch red tubing coming from the
                    Brake Proportioning Valve. Reference
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9550803">Figure 3</hotlnk>
                    for required parts.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Only black bulk tubing is available in Service Parts.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install floor access panel and floor mat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install driver's seat and torque mounting bolts to 155 to 190 INCH- POUNDS.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install seat belts back onto seat and torque mounting bolts to 25 to 35
                    FOOT-POUNDS.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect air lines at seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform Air Check, Steps a. through f. to verify system is okay.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
